---
// src/pages/cane-toad-removal/index.astro
// Main service page — targets: "cane toad removal", "toad removal service", "cane toad exterminator"
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ContentImage from '../../components/ContentImage.astro';
import canetoadInYard from '../../assets/images/canetoad-in-yard.jpg';
import nightRemovalHeadlamp from '../../assets/images/cane-toad-night-collection.png';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cane Toad Removal Service Florida | Licensed Bufo Toad Exterminators"
  description="Find licensed cane toad removal services across South Florida. Vetted providers, same-week availability, serving all major counties. Get a free quote today."
>

  <div class="urgency">
    <strong>⚠️ Pet owners:</strong> Cane toad toxin can kill a dog in 15 minutes. <a href="/cane-toad-dog-poisoning/">Read the emergency response guide</a> before your pet encounters a toad.
  </div>

  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-media">
      <ContentImage
        src={canetoadInYard}
        alt="Cane toad on a Florida lawn at night — typical conditions where licensed trappers perform hand collection and property assessment"
        class="hero-image"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <h1>Cane Toad Removal Services in South Florida</h1>
      <p>We connect South Florida homeowners with licensed, experienced cane toad removal professionals. All providers in our network are FWC-registered nuisance wildlife trappers with proven track records in bufo toad control.</p>
      <a href="#get-quote" class="btn btn-lg">Request a Free Quote →</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="lead-form-wrap" id="get-quote">
    <h2>Get Connected with a Local Provider</h2>
    <p>Enter your zip code and we'll match you with a licensed removal professional in your area — typically within the hour.</p>
    <iframe data-tally-src="https://tally.so/embed/0QL69P?alignLeft=1&hideTitle=1&transparentBackground=1&dynamicHeight=1" width="100%" height="320" frameborder="0" marginheight="0" marginwidth="0" title="Homeowner Request Form"></iframe>
  </div>

  <div class="content">

    <h2>What Cane Toad Removal Involves</h2>
    <p>Cane toad removal is a specialist service that requires understanding toad behavior, breeding cycles, and property-specific risk factors. It's distinct from general pest control — most exterminators are not equipped to handle bufo toad populations effectively.</p>
    <p>Licensed providers in our network offer:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Initial property assessment</strong> — identifying toad hotspots, entry points, water sources, and habitat conditions that attract toads</li>
      <li><strong>Hand collection</strong> — night-time removal visits when toads are most active and visible</li>
      <li><strong>Egg string removal</strong> — cane toads lay eggs in pools, ponds, and any standing water; removing egg strings prevents next-generation infestations</li>
      <li><strong>Habitat modification advice</strong> — reducing lighting, ground cover, and water features that attract toads</li>
      <li><strong>Barrier fencing</strong> — physical exclusion barriers around pool cages, lanais, and yard perimeters</li>
      <li><strong>Recurring maintenance</strong> — monthly visits to keep populations controlled throughout toad season</li>
    </ul>

    <figure class="content-figure">
      <ContentImage
        src={nightRemovalHeadlamp}
        alt="Technician with headlamp locating cane toads along a Florida yard at night during a professional removal visit"
      />
      <figcaption>Effective removal relies on night-time visits with good lighting—when cane toads are active and easier to find safely.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>One-Time vs. Recurring Service</h2>
    <p>A single removal visit will significantly reduce the toad population on your property — often by 80% or more in one night. However, toads from neighboring properties and new hatchlings will reinfest over time without follow-up. For most South Florida homeowners, monthly recurring service is the most effective long-term solution.</p>
    <p>Typical pricing: initial visit $120–$190, recurring monthly service $100–$170/month depending on property size. <a href="/cane-toad-removal-cost/">See detailed pricing →</a></p>

    <h2>How to Choose a Removal Provider</h2>
    <p>Not all wildlife removal companies are equally equipped for cane toad work. When evaluating a provider, ask:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Are you FWC-registered as a nuisance wildlife trapper?</li>
      <li>Do you do night-time removal visits? (Daytime visits are far less effective)</li>
      <li>Do you remove egg strings from water features?</li>
      <li>What's included in the initial assessment?</li>
      <li>Do you offer a recurring maintenance plan?</li>
    </ul>
    <p>All providers in our network have been vetted against these criteria. When you submit your zip code above, we match you with qualified professionals in your specific area.</p>

    <h2>Service Areas</h2>
    <p>Our provider network covers all major South Florida counties. Select yours for area-specific information:</p>
    <div class="geo-grid">
      <div class="geo-card"><a href="/cane-toad-removal-miami-dade/">Miami-Dade County</a></div>
      <div class="geo-card"><a href="/cane-toad-removal-broward-county/">Broward County</a></div>
      <div class="geo-card"><a href="/cane-toad-removal-palm-beach-county/">Palm Beach County</a></div>
      <div class="geo-card"><a href="/cane-toad-removal-collier-county/">Collier County / Naples</a></div>
      <div class="geo-card"><a href="/cane-toad-removal-lee-county/">Lee County / Cape Coral</a></div>
      <div class="geo-card"><a href="/cane-toad-removal-west-palm-beach/">West Palm Beach</a></div>
      <div class="geo-card"><a href="/cane-toad-removal-parkland/">Parkland & Weston</a></div>
      <div class="geo-card"><a href="/cane-toad-removal-martin-st-lucie/">Treasure Coast</a></div>
    </div>

    <h2>Related Resources</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/cane-toad-florida/">Complete guide to cane toads in Florida</a></li>
      <li><a href="/cane-toad-dog-poisoning/">Cane toad dog poisoning: symptoms and emergency response</a></li>
      <li><a href="/how-to-get-rid-of-cane-toads/">How to get rid of cane toads yourself</a></li>
      <li><a href="/cane-toad-trap/">Best cane toad traps</a></li>
      <li><a href="/toad-proof-fencing/">Toad proof fencing options</a></li>
      <li><a href="/cane-toad-vs-southern-toad/">How to identify cane toads vs. native toads</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details>
        <summary>How quickly can a provider come out?</summary>
        <p>Most providers in our network can schedule within 2–5 days for standard visits. Emergency same-day service is available from some providers at a premium rate. Submit your zip code above and we'll let you know availability in your area.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Do I need to be home during the removal?</summary>
        <p>For the initial assessment, yes — your provider will want to walk the property with you to identify problem areas and discuss your specific situation. For recurring maintenance visits, many homeowners give their provider gate access so visits can happen at night without the homeowner being present.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Will removal harm my pets or children?</summary>
        <p>Professional cane toad removal is entirely safe for people and pets. Providers use humane collection methods — no pesticides, traps, or chemicals are involved. The toads are euthanized off-site in accordance with FWC guidelines.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What's the difference between cane toads and bufo toads?</summary>
        <p>"Bufo toad" is simply a common nickname for the cane toad, derived from its former scientific name <em>Bufo marinus</em> (now reclassified as <em>Rhinella marina</em>). They are the same species. You'll see both names used interchangeably by South Florida homeowners and removal services.</p>
      </details>
    </div>

  </div>

</BaseLayout>
